{"query": "What problem or limitation in previous work motivated the extension of the semiclassical model of the collective atomic recoil laser, and what methods or results from previous work are used in this extension?", "function": "Motivation", "result": {"function": "Motivation", "winner": {"id": 0, "paper_id": "cond-mat/0102360", "title": "Quantum effects in the collective light scattering by coherent atomic\n  recoil in a Bose-Einstein condensate", "authors": "N. PiovellaM. GatelliR. Bonifacio", "year": "2001", "fit": 0.8, "topicality": 0.9, "retrieval_score": 0.86, "quote": "We extend the semiclassical model of the collective atomic recoil laser", "why": "sufficient"}, "answer_sentence": "The extension of the semiclassical model of the collective atomic recoil laser was motivated by the need to include quantum mechanical effects, particularly for cases where the average atomic momentum is less than the recoil momentum. The semiclassical CARL model is used as a foundation, with its equations reducing to the Maxwell-Bloch equations under certain conditions, and its results recovered in the limit of large average photon scattering per atom (cond-mat/0102360).", "verdicts": [{"id": 0, "paper_id": "cond-mat/0102360", "fit": 0.8, "topicality": 0.9, "retrieval": 0.86, "supports": true, "invalid_reason": "", "evidence_ok": true, "on_topic_ok": true, "cue_hint": false}, {"id": 3, "paper_id": "hep-th/0103228", "fit": 0.0, "topicality": 0.0, "retrieval": 0.841, "supports": false, "invalid_reason": "no_quote", "evidence_ok": false, "on_topic_ok": false, "cue_hint": false}, {"id": 4, "paper_id": "hep-ph/0102144", "fit": 0.0, "topicality": 0.0, "retrieval": 0.84, "supports": false, "invalid_reason": "no_quote", "evidence_ok": false, "on_topic_ok": false, "cue_hint": false}, {"id": 5, "paper_id": "hep-ph/0103129", "fit": 0.0, "topicality": 0.0, "retrieval": 0.84, "supports": false, "invalid_reason": "no_quote", "evidence_ok": false, "on_topic_ok": false, "cue_hint": false},